[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     attributes like dosage and route, and returns RxNorm concept IDs for the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     detected medications. Passing full label context (not just drug name and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     dosage) gives the model surrounding clinical information (route, frequency,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     prescriber context) that helps disambiguate similar drug names and confirm
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the correct dosage form.
[0m[49m[39m  447, 449[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  448, 450[0m:[39m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 449     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         drug_name: The drug name extracted from the label (e.g., "Amoxicillin")
[0m[49m[38;5;9m- 450     [0m:[38;5;9m[49m         dosage:    The dosage extracted from the label (e.g., "500mg")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         normalized_fields: The output of normalize_rx_fields. All field values
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                            are concatenated to form the input text for the NLP model.
[0m[49m[39m  451, 453[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  452, 454[0m:[39m[49m     Returns:
